## Summary
Add parallel-bucket visualization to the DAG renderer, enabling users to see which units can run concurrently, identify the critical path, and estimate wall-clock time.

## Context
The DAG renderer (F24-F28) provides an interactive graph view, but project managers and engineers need a **schedule-oriented view** that answers: "What can run in parallel? What's on the critical path? How long will this take?" This PR adds the Bucket View — a swimlane-based parallel schedule computed from the DAG topology.

## Changes
- **`src/lib/dag/buckets.ts`** — Core computation module with:
  - `topoSortWithLevels()`: Kahn's algorithm returning topological order + longest-path level assignment
  - `computeCriticalPath()`: Forward/backward CPM pass with zero-slack tracing (8 steps: forward ES/EF, backward LF/LS, slack calculation, path extraction)
  - `computeBucketSchedule()`: Groups nodes by level into parallel buckets with wall-clock duration per bucket
  - `computeWallClock()`: Convenience function for per-bucket and total wall-clock estimates
- **`src/pages/dag/buckets.astro`** — New page with:
  - Swimlane layout showing each parallel bucket as a horizontal section
  - Status badges, duration tags, and concurrency badges per node
  - Critical-path nodes highlighted with red borders and "critical" labels
  - Timeline header showing proportional wall-clock bars
  - Concurrency analysis panel (largest bucket, parallel efficiency, savings vs sequential)
  - Toggle link between Graph View (`/dag/`) and Bucket View (`/dag/buckets/`)
- **`src/pages/dag/index.astro`** — Added "Bucket View" toggle button in legend bar
- **`tests/dag-buckets.test.ts`** — 36 tests covering topo sort, CPM critical path, bucket grouping, wall-clock computation, and invariants across 5 fixture DAG topologies (linear chain, fork-join diamond, duration-variance diamond, empty, single node)
- **`vitest.config.ts`** — Test runner configuration for projects-landing
- **`data/dag-data.json`** — Added `estimatedHours` to all 15 Epic F units

## Testing
```bash
# Run the full test suite (54 tests total — 36 new bucket + 18 existing)
cd sites/projects-landing && bun test

# Preview the bucket view
cd sites/projects-landing && bun run dev
# Then visit http://localhost:4321/dag/buckets
# Or click "Bucket View" from the graph view at /dag/
```

